<title>
Air Bleeding of Clutch System
</title>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Brake fluid (Clutch fluid) is extremely damaging to paint. If fluid should accidentally touch painted surface, immediately wipe fluid from paint and clean painted surface.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
When operating the clutch pedal for air bleeding, after releasing the clutch pedal, be sure to wait 1 second or more before depressing it again. Otherwise, the oil seal of operating cylinder will be damaged, resulting in oil leakage.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<ptxt>
Bleed air from clutch system.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Refer to 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4106004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
.
</ptxt>
